/**

 @page "CCA - Peano's Integration into the a Simplified Common Component Architecture"
 
 !!! Prepare Your Component For CCA 
 
 Once before you start to work with CCA, you have to do some preparation steps.
 These steps have to be done once and only once.   
 Run the following script on the terminal to generate all the glue code:
 \code
 cd Peano's src directory
 java -jar ../releases/tools/scicode-compiler.jar -I peano/integration/cca/standard-ports.sidl --naming de.tum.scicode.sidl.plugins.Peano -L xml-c++   -l libmultigrid.so peano/applications/poisson/multigrid/cca/MultigridBatchJob.sidl 
 java -jar ../releases/tools/scicode-compiler.jar -I peano/integration/cca/standard-ports.sidl --naming de.tum.scicode.sidl.plugins.Peano -L c++-ports peano/applications/poisson/multigrid/cca/MultigridBatchJob.sidl 
 java -jar ../releases/tools/scicode-compiler.jar -I peano/integration/cca/standard-ports.sidl --naming de.tum.scicode.sidl.plugins.Peano -L c++-plain peano/applications/poisson/multigrid/cca/MultigridBatchJob.sidl 
 \endcode

 Sometimes, this doesn't work as the jar file depends on other jar files. In 
 this case, you might try: 
 \code
 cd Peano's src directory
 java -classpath ../releases/tools/scicode-compiler.jar:../releases/tools/jargs.jar de.tum.scicode.sidl.Compiler -I peano/integration/cca/standard-ports.sidl --naming de.tum.scicode.sidl.plugins.Peano -L xml-c++   -l libmultigrid.so peano/applications/poisson/multigrid/cca/MultigridBatchJob.sidl 
 java -classpath ../releases/tools/scicode-compiler.jar:../releases/tools/jargs.jar de.tum.scicode.sidl.Compiler -I peano/integration/cca/standard-ports.sidl --naming de.tum.scicode.sidl.plugins.Peano -L c++-ports peano/applications/poisson/multigrid/cca/MultigridBatchJob.sidl 
 java -classpath ../releases/tools/scicode-compiler.jar:../releases/tools/jargs.jar de.tum.scicode.sidl.Compiler -I peano/integration/cca/standard-ports.sidl --naming de.tum.scicode.sidl.plugins.Peano -L c++-plain peano/applications/poisson/multigrid/cca/MultigridBatchJob.sidl 
 \endcode
 Also, adding the argument $-v$ might give you some hints what actually goes wrong.

 Include the directory peano/integration/cca into your build path and recompile 
 your code with $-DCCA$ into a shared lib. For this, Peano's setup script has 
 already prepared a makefile. 

 */
 
 
